      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(config): allow explicit main agent bindings when agents.list is non-empty",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRoute bindings to the implicit default agent `\"main\"` are rejected at config load and silently deleted by `doctor --fix` when `agents.list` is non-empty. This breaks the documented multi-agent config pattern where a few ACP agents are listed while `\"main\"` handles everything else.\n\nThe fix treats `DEFAULT_AGENT_ID` (`\"main\"`) as a valid explicit binding target in both config validation and doctor pruning, consistent with how routing already uses it as the universal fallback.\n\nCloses #89412\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: Config load throws `Unknown agent id \"main\" (not in agents.list)` and `doctor --fix` silently removes valid `main` bindings from disk when `agents.list` is non-empty.\n\n**Real environment tested**: macOS 26.6 (Darwin arm64), Node v22.22.0, OpenClaw source checkout at `2d61521bd`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\n# Live verification: schema accepts 'main' as binding target with non-empty agents.list\nnode --import tsx -e \"\nimport { OpenClawSchema } from './src/config/zod-schema.js';\nconst config = {\n  agents: { list: [{ id: 'codex' }, { id: 'claude' }] },\n  bindings: [{ match: { channel: 'webchat' }, agentId: 'main' }]\n};\ntry {\n  const parsed = OpenClawSchema.parse(config);\n  console.log('PASS: config with main bindings accepted');\n} catch (e) {\n  console.log('FAIL:', e.issues.slice(0,3).map(i => i.path.join('.') + ': ' + i.message).join('; '));\n}\n\"\n\n# Unit tests\nnpx tsx node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run src/config/config.schema-regressions.test.ts\nnpx tsx node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run src/commands/doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts\nnpx tsx node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-config-migrate.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\nLive runtime verification (before vs after fix):\n\n```\n# BEFORE fix (main branch):\n$ node --import tsx -e \"...\"\nBEFORE-FIX: FAIL: bindings.0.agentId: Unknown agent id \\\"main\\\" (not in agents.list).\n\n# AFTER fix (this branch):\n$ node --import tsx -e \"...\"\nPASS: config with main bindings accepted\n```\n\nAll existing tests pass — no regressions:\n\n```\n ✓ config.schema-regressions.test.ts — 32 tests passed\n ✓ doctor-legacy-config.migrations.test.ts — 51 tests passed\n ✓ legacy-config-migrate.test.ts — 103 tests passed\n\n Test Files  3 passed (3)\n      Tests  186 passed (186)\n```\n\nLint clean: `oxlint` 0 warnings 0 errors across both changed files.\n\n**Observed result after fix**: Configs with `agents.list: [{id: \"codex\"}, {id: \"claude\"}]` and `bindings` targeting `agentId: \"main\"` no longer fail config load and are no longer stripped by `doctor --fix`. Genuinely missing agent ids (not in list and not `\"main\"`) continue to be rejected/pruned.\n\n**What was not tested**: Full end-to-end gateway startup with the fixed config (local CI only).\n\n@clawsweeper review\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/main-agent-binding-rejection",
